    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.7.0\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNot related to vim\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nPopOs 21.10\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\ngnvim\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nBuild from source\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\nOpen [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/1f1a65a9e4c602cd80458b213c28eadbdb5b1de1/test/functional/legacy/044_099_regexp_multibyte_magic_spec.lua#L14-L33) file and scroll into those lines (lines 28 and 29 to be exact) in a GUI and neovim will send invalid UTF-8 in a `grid_line` event.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWork as documented, e.g. send valid UTF-8.\r\n\r\nWhat this should be in practice is up to debate I suppose. For reference, gedit shows a warning and displays the bytes sequence with red color:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4594126/169686414-4e97a45b-7b8b-470f-b1cc-e321abcbd95d.png)\r\n\r\nAnother solid option could be to send the \"replacement character\" (e.g.  U+FFFD ï¿½) in place of invalid UTF-8 data.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nNeovim sends invalid UTF-8 in `grid_line` event.\r\n\r\nThis is how the TUI renders those invalid lines:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4594126/169685993-ce5e3dfa-4a3d-4da7-ae13-c01e7a6f2608.png)\r\n\r\nWheres the log file with `-u NONE`: [nvim.log](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/files/8749078/nvim.log)\r\n ",
